The '''Queen Charlotte Islands caribou''' or '''Dawson's caribou''' (''Rangifer tarandus dawsoni'') is an [[extinct]] [[subspecies]] of the [[Reindeer|reindeer]] (or the caribou in [[North America]]) that once lived on [[Graham Island]], the largest of the [[Haida Gwaii]] islands in [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]]. Possible causes of extinction include [[habitat destruction]], introduced disease and [[hunting|overhunting]]. It was gray in appearance. The last three caribou were killed in 1908 and can be seen at the [[Royal British Columbia Museum]], where their pelts and bones are preserved and displayed.<ref>[http://www.speciesatrisk.bc.ca/node/7955 Dawson Caribou] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407124051/http://www.speciesatrisk.bc.ca/node/7955 |date=2014-04-07 }}, Species at Risk</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.canadiangeographic.ca/magazine/nd07/indepth/peary_caribou.asp|title=Caribou in Canada|publisher=Canadian Geographic|date=2007-11-01 |accessdate=2016-06-16}}</ref> Recent analysis of [[mtDNA]] suggests that the Queen Charlotte Islands caribou was not genetically distinct from the subspecies from the Canadian mainland.<ref>Byun, S.A.; B.F. Koop, and T.E. Reimchen. (2002). Evolution of the Dawson caribou (''Rangifer tarandus dawsoni''). ''Can. J. Zool.'' 80(5): 956–960. {{doi|10.1139/z02-062}}. NRC Canada. [http://rparticle.web-p.cisti.nrc.ca/rparticle/AbstractTemplateServlet?journal=cjz&volume=80&year=&issue=&msno=z02-062&calyLang=eng online]{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
