{{italic title}} {{Infobox website |name = Way to Go |logo = |logocaption = |screenshot = |collapsible = |collapsetext = |caption = |url = http://a-way-to-go.com/ |commercial = |type = Web-based interactive film |registration = |language = English/French |content license = |owner = National Film Board of Canada/France Télévisions |author = Vincent Morisset, Philippe Lambert, Édouard Lanctôt-Benoit and Caroline Robert (AATOAA) |launch date = 2015 |alexa = |revenue = |current status = |footnotes = }} '''''Way to Go''''' (French: '''''Jusqu'ici''''') is a 2015 Canada/France [[interactive film]] and [[virtual reality]] web-based experience created by the [[Montreal]] digital studio AATOAA ({{Interlanguage link multi|Vincent Morisset|fr}}, Philippe Lambert, Édouard Lanctôt-Benoit and Caroline Robert) and produced by [[National Film Board of Canada]] ([[Hugues Sweeney]]) and [[France Télévisions]]. The production lets users take a virtual walk in the woods, through a combination of animation and [[immersive video]].<ref name="Collins">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/beta/arts/vincent-morisset-will-convince-you-that-websites-are-works-of-art-1.3453962|title=Vincent Morisset will convince you that websites are works of art|last=Collins|first=Leah|date=19 February 2016|work=CBC Arts|accessdate=10 May 2016}}</ref>
==User experience== In February 2016, ''[[Animation World Network]]'''s Jennifer Wolfe described the user experience as follows: {{Quote|Users pilot a block-headed, hand-drawn avatar through the experience, they can pause to examine the world around them, sometimes triggering a strange tunnel vision effect that shifts the perspective to a first-person POV. During the seemingly endless journey, the world oscillates between black-and-white live action and a colored, lo-res digital mode. Eighty-three custom shaders change lights, grain and visual effects in real time while thousands of sounds are live mixed and synced to user interaction. The music score itself, composed by Philippe Lambert, is generative, responding to the viewer’s pace as they amble (or fly) through the forest.<ref name=Wolfe>{{cite news|url=http://www.awn.com/news/nfb-releases-vincent-morisset-s-way-go-online|title=NFB Releases Vincent Morisset’s ‘Way to Go’ Online|last=Wolfe|first=Jennifer|date=16 February 2016|work=Animation World Network|accessdate=10 May 2016}}</ref>}}
==Reception== ''Way to Go'' was unveiled as VR installation at the [[2015 Sundance Film Festival]]’s New Frontier showcase.<ref name=Wolfe/> Awards to date include three [[2016 Webby Awards]], Webby and People's Voice awards in the Web/NetArt category as well as the Webby Award for Online Film & Video/VR: Gaming, Interactive or Real-Time.<ref name="Wong">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/webby-wins-2016-1.3553650|title=Webby Awards 2016 winners include The Weeknd, the NFB|last=Wong|first=Jessica|date=26 April 2016|work=CBC News|accessdate=10 May 2016}}</ref> On 27 April 2015, it was named Cutting Edge Project of the Week at the [[Favourite Website Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefwa.com/adobe/tcea/way-to-go|title=Way to Go|work=Favourite Websites Awards|accessdate=10 May 2016}}</ref>
